import React, {Component} from 'react' import Form from 'react-bootstrap/Form' import Col from 'react-bootstrap/Col' import Row from 'react-bootstrap/Row' import Button from 'react-bootstrap/Button' import ReactDatePicker from 'react-datepicker' import "react-datepicker/dist/react-datepicker.css"; import * as yup from 'yup' const SignupSchema = yup.object().shape({ username: yup.string() .required('Username is required'), password: yup.string() .min(8, 'Passwords needs to be longer than 8 characters') .matches(/[a-z]/, 'Password needs at least 1 lowercase character.') .matches(/[A-Z]/, 'Password needs at least 1 uppercase character.') .matches(/[1-9]/, 'Password needs at least a number.'), confirmPassword: yup.string() .equalTo(yup.ref('password'), "Passwords don't match."), firstName: yup.string() .max(50, 'Too Long!') .required('Required'), lastName: yup.string() .max(50, 'Too Long!') .required('Required'), email: yup.string() .email('Invalid email') .required('Required'), }); class SignUpPage extends Component { render() { const startDate = new Date(); return (
Username Password Email OR First Name Last Name Middle Suffix Date Of Birth
) } } export default SignUpPage
